##Girl in Wuhan, China, writes suicide note after catching pneumonia

MICRO-SIGNAL YITIAOTV

Feature description, a short original video every day, every day to tell a moving story, every day selected human beauty, every day to live a better life with me.

Element Element

Wuhan Girl Su Su,

One of the lucky ones who survived the new pneumonia.

She is an ordinary white-collar worker,

On January 14th of this year,

Diagnosed on January 19, he was quarantined at home,

Because of many reports that "the disease will suddenly deteriorate, "

She wrote her suicide note in tears.

On January 30th, her symptoms subsided,

The mother who was infected at the same time,

To pump each other up, to self-medicate, to isolate,

And he was cured.

She wrote an article about her experience of the "epidemic" of the war,

One is published here in full with exclusive permission.

She told us that for people with mild illness,

The virus isn't that bad,

It's like having a cold,

What's really scary is when the virus comes,

The Pride and Prejudice.

"May all of you come back safe and sound from the ravages of the past,

May people be in awe of nature and never give up."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Su Su Su home is located in the community, away from the South China Seafood Market a wall

Now that I think about it, I'm not really sure when I got it. Before January 14th, I had no symptoms, not even the symptoms of a common cold. On January 11, I set off for Shanghai for a few days. On January 14, I was on my way back to Shanghai Hongqiao Railway Station. Looking back now, I am glad that no one offered me a seat at that time, no one helped me, I am glad that I just wear a mask, it should not affect others.

The only thing I was worried about was sitting next to me on the way back to Wuhan on the high-speed train, taking my three grandchildren from Nantong to Jingzhou for the New Year. I gave them snacks, disposable slippers and a few words, i wonder if they're still okay. Looking back now, I really blame myself and care about the old man. If it wasn't too late for me to understand the epidemic, who would want to be a bad person?

In fact, on the way back to Wuhan that day, my mother also sent me a message, saying that she was at home, feeling unwell, cold, dizziness, etc. . At that time, when the flu was raging, I thought she just caught a cold, comforted a few words, did not take it seriously at all.

On the evening of the 14th, he arrived in Wuhan and rested at home for several days. On the 15th and 16th, I was in a particularly bad state. I had no appetite and no sense of smell or taste. I could only recognize sweet taste. I had a cold sweat and was wet with sweat when I slept. I should have had a low fever, but I didn't pay much attention. I didn't cough or have a running nose.

New Pneumonia has been listed in accordance with the legal provisions of "Class B infectious diseases" (including Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome, AIDS, hepatitis) , according to Class A infectious diseases (including cholera, plague) for prevention and control.

On Jan. 16, I scrolled my Weibo and noticed that some people were starting to get a little more alert and concerned about the fact that their father had a new type of pneumonia and was not being admitted to a hospital. I have friends who care enough to send me to the hospital for a check-up. But I think I usually good health, rarely catch a cold, although the whole body during the day, but wake up, but also feel good mental state, so firmly believe that he is only a minor illness, after two days will be fine. It was not until the 19th that I took the chance to do a basic check-up.

It was 3:00 in the afternoon, before the hospital was full, and by 5:30, I was one of the doctor's last patients. The woman doctor asked a few questions, such as whether there is no fever and cough, my answer is not obvious, just want to do a check-up, the doctor said: that only a CT can determine. When I got in line for a CT scan, I realized that, like me, there were a lot of self-doubters, and the entire CT room hallway was full.

The CT results aren't due for another two hours, so I'M GONNA drive up to Hanyang and pick up my dad. Dad came to Wuhan that day by bus from his hometown with a bag of snake-skin preserved meat and special products. I was already beginning to feel weak and weak, so after I picked him up, I didn't get off the bus to help him carry things, and I didn't say much either, took him straight home, didn't have time to eat dinner, went to the hospital to get the results.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Su-su described her situation to her friend afterwards

Back at the hospital, I saw some people get the CT results, elated to go, some people are still waiting in line anxiously. It was nearly nine o'clock in the evening when it was my turn, and I couldn't believe my eyes when I saw the sign that said "infectious lesion in the lower right lung. ". To confirm, I immediately went back to the clinic to continue the line, ask the emergency room doctor.

At that time, the hospital emergency room was already crowded at night and long lines began to form. The doctor saw my film, and asked me, before the doctor why did not let you check the blood? I am still a little confused, the doctor a little helpless, said, now you hurry to check the blood, I hope you do not all the results are negative. I asked, why? The doctor said, if the results are all negative, that means you this is a new type of pneumonia ah!

At that time, I did not understand what logic, wait an hour, the blood results also came out, to ask the doctor, the doctor changed shifts, so I re-registered, obediently line up. Finally wait for me, after the change of a doctor, I guess is not too experienced, also did not give me a clear answer. I didn't dare to ask, but I was pretty sure by then.

January 19th was a long day. When I got home, I found that my parents had fallen asleep. I quickly got my father up and went to another room alone. I Guess Dad was lying then, the next day still said he was hungry to get up for breakfast, with us to use a bathroom. I felt that it was not proper for everyone to live together, so I ordered him to evacuate and go back to his hometown at once instead of staying in Wuhan.

At the same time, I am very worried about my mother's condition, she caught cold earlier than me. She didn't show any signs of trouble during those days, and even kept up with her work and housework. She made dinner the Day Dad came home. The News said that only the gold and Silver Pool Hospital centralized treatment of the hospital fever patients, I quickly took my mother to the gold and Silver Pool Hospital.

To the hospital just know, the hospital will not receive their own in-patient. That day I was still weak, let my mother do CT and blood test. Sure enough, mom was diagnosed, and it was a double lung infection.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The test report of Su Su's mother

While waiting for the results, I witnessed another family, with their sick family members, seeking admission to a hospital, because the entire Wuhan Hospital had been run all over, none of them were admitted, and their condition was already very serious. However, all the hospital can do is appease and persuade them to leave.

I dragged the weak body, with my mother left the hospital, still returned to our home near the Xinhua Hospital. I was very much hope that my mother can be admitted to the hospital, because from the CT results to see her more serious, and the elderly, after all, the physical function will be a little worse.

By this time, the hospital was significantly more full than it had been the day before. A lot of people start to feel bad because they've been in line for so long. When I showed the results of both my mother and myself to the doctor, the young doctor was inexperienced and called the director, who looked at them and made it clear that he had contracted a new type of pneumonia because there was no nucleic acid reagent, we can only diagnose from CT and screen for known viruses. He told us that at this time, all hospitals could not have beds. The best way was to go home and isolate the patient by yourself. After that, there was no need to lose the infusion, because there was no specific medicine for this disease, some prescription medications (OSELTAMIVIR FOR A & B and the antibiotic Motrin) May help.

I could feel the commotion and tension in the crowd outside the clinic, presumably because the doctors had diagnosed the new form of pneumonia. At that time, I was actually not nervous at all, because so many people want to be diagnosed, like us, at least half of it... the human instinct is: If everyone is the same, things just don't seem that scary.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 20, Su Su waited with her mother for an injection until 6 p.m

On the day of the last injection with my mother, the entire transfusion area was also full. Seeing that many people in my friends'circle were still treating the epidemic with a jokey attitude, I wrote down my situation truthfully and sent a friend's circle, to alert my friends.

I did not expect this friend circle caused such a big disturbance, within an hour, the city's wechat group has spread, even spread to the provinces, my mobile phone messages all exploded in an instant. I was physically and psychologically stressed, do not want to browse and reply to the message, this circle of friends deleted.

Most people probably thought they were too far gone to know what was really going on in the hospital. When I came home from the hospital to buy medicine at the pharmacy downstairs, I reminded the teller that she must wear a mask. A man next to me laughed at me and said I was too nervous until I said I had been diagnosed and he thought I was joking.

From the night of January 20, it was really felt that everyone's attention and tension. The hospital's problems began to be highlighted and taken seriously, and various policy messages followed. Academician Zhong Nanshan spoke to confirm that people passed on from one person to another. Finally, everyone began to face up to and deal with all this.

Then I had the worst New Year's eve of my life. No more marriage, no more family reunion, no more rich new year meal, no more relatives around and New Year blessing, only full of fear and anxiety, even insomnia all night.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Su-su said it was "a feast for her and her mother on New Year's Eve. "

While crying, he wrote a suicide note for his sister, regretting that he had many things to do before he had time to do them. He spent the whole night thinking about his short and happy first half of his life, fearing that his lungs would suddenly turn white, as some reports say, at any time breathing difficulties, at any time life is in danger, at any time will leave this beautiful world..

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
SU-SU's suicide note at the time

I cried in secret because my mother's test results were more serious than mine, and I didn't want to upset her. She was older, didn't belong to a group, and didn't receive negative or frightening messages about the epidemic that I didn't pass on to her. Throughout the isolation process, she was very calm, basically I let her check, let her injection, home quarantine, disinfection, and so on, all follow my instructions and arrangements, from the beginning to the end without any depression.

In the home isolation day, I was concerned about the progress of the epidemic and from the humor of the people across the country, while also doing self-psychological counseling, time passed quickly. Because of the loss of taste and appetite, I can not eat anything, unconsciously lost five or six pounds, but also in recent years for the first time successfully restored to 93 pounds of the ideal weight.

By the evening of January 26th, it was clear that my appetite had returned. For more than 10 days, the first initiative to find food to fill the stomach, night to the kitchen to salvage a bit of food, unexpectedly very happy and satisfied. The moment I regained my sense of taste, it was like I was born again.

My Mom's seizures and her recovery are basically in sync with mine. Summarize the symptoms of onset:

1. Loss of taste and appetite, and even nausea

2, chills, accompanied by muscle soreness, weakness and even shivering, cold sweat during sleep;

Dizziness, weakness, similar to a cold;

4, the initial (the first week) sputum in the lungs, just began to white, medium (onset about 10 days) green, with blood, or even full of blood, late (about 15 days) blood loss, phlegm also slowly disappeared.

With this new type of pneumonia, some people do not have a fever, such as my mother and I almost did not have a fever the whole time. Critically ill patients will basically have a fever, but most people are mild, the first four or five days of physical symptoms feel more obvious, after the disease is not obvious. As soon as appetite returns and physical strength returns, victory in the War of resistance can almost be declared.

My father returned home in time because of quarantine, more than 10 days, no symptoms, from infection.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Su Su Su and her mother took the medicine when they were quarantined at home, Lotus Qingwen was bought by herself, Oseltamivir and Moxifloxacin were prescribed by doctors

These days, I play the role of online consultation, many people themselves or their family and friends were infected, have come to seek medical treatment, seek experience, I answer one by one, I would like to tell you is:

1. In the absence of a confirmed nucleic acid diagnosis, CT scans and screening for known infectious viruses are 99% conclusive. Because of the scarcity of nucleic acid reagents and the high hardware requirements of applications, it is almost impossible to diagnose in this way, except in critically ill patients.

None of the people I've been around with symptoms have had a chance to be diagnosed with a nucleic acid test. I myself have been anti-japanese virus for more than half a month now. Although I have registered my condition at the front desk of the hospital, I am not on the list of this report.

2. Going to the hospital to get the care you need is difficult at this stage, and the pressure on doctors to take care of you is enormous. It is better to be prepared to fight their own psychological, besides, the hospital all kinds of lines, suspected of being sick for you, the body is more difficult, as at home rest.

3. How is this disease treated for most people with mild illness? In a word, rely on their own resistance. There is no right medicine, the best medicine, is their own mentality.

Think of this more than 10 days, a good state of mind, do not feel oneself in the treatment, the meal to eat, drink medicine, brush the phone, very relaxed, but also conducive to physical recovery. But when you stare at the negative news, you are so nervous that you feel as if you are facing the end of your life at any moment. You can't eat or sleep well. You search for symptoms and spread bad information that creates an atmosphere of fear. Now think, too nervous and negative, is to resist the condition of the biggest obstacle.

4, be sure to do a good job of prevention, do not think that the virus is far from their own, it is best to develop the habit of daily disinfection. Now every corner of my home every day ultraviolet car disinfection, 84 spray, alcohol wipe, boiling water chopsticks every day. Take alcohol with you when you leave the house, and spray anything you touch.

After 16 days of war, victory is in sight, many people ask me how I feel, in fact, I want to tell you not to be afraid, this disease is not so terrible. The spread is rapid, but the threat to life is not so great, the most frightening is their own fear and imagination of the unknown virus, rather than the virus itself.

Although at the end of the war, we had too many questions, such as: Will there be antibodies after recovery? Will you be re-infected or re-infected in the short or long term? When will there be prophylactic drugs? WHEN DOES THE BATTLE END? ... We, as the vanguard of this outbreak, would like to know, and that is the question we are all about to face.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Su Su Su was cured and consulted on the Internet

These days, I feel the love of the world. Some friends sent large New Year red envelopes, some colleagues do not know where to hear that I am out of drugs, pharmacies are closed all over the city to buy drugs, but also the Avatar to help me get the drugs, and some friends at risk to send mask supplies..

Looking at the various abuses of Hubei region on the Internet, I really feel quite funny. This epidemic, Wuhan people made a lot of sacrifices, but also bear a lot of blame. The suffering Wuhan people really do not have the energy and time to respond to you, but it does not mean serious up we will lose.

At the same time, I also noticed that there was good news in my circle of friends that the friend's mother, who had been in hospital for more than 20 days with more severe symptoms than me and my mother, had been cured.

Vegetarian friend's mother's experience of fighting "epidemic" , her symptoms are much more serious than vegetarian mother and daughter

When you experience a brush with death, really, from that moment on, everything will be relieved, to live healthy, more important than anything. If you don't experience loss, who knows how good it is to be together again?

After so many days of isolation at home, I realized that lying down every day wasn't so much of a dream. Only to contribute to society, can play their own energy, is the greatest meaning of life.

I didn't realize how much I needed, so much so that I couldn't leave them for a day, the delivery service, the sanitation workers, the neighborhood sanitation workers, the supermarket cashiers, the taxi drivers, and so on.

I didn't even realize, that the front-line health care workers, they were the guardians of life. In the real battle against death, they were in front of us. And those volunteers who are willing to contribute, you are the brightest light in the crowd!

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Su-su and her colleagues organized a voluntary donation of medical supplies

At this time, only really understand that sentence: All for me, I for all! I hope we can work together to restore the normal society as soon as possible, after all, few people are not burdened with such as mortgage, car, parents, children and other heavy life pressure.

Wuhan has only inadvertently become a page of the textbook of nature's warning to mankind. This is not a city of Wuhan's fault, each of us have the obligation and responsibility to bear in mind and bear this lesson.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The fatality rate is one of the biggest concerns of the epidemic, and there have been a number of recent oral experiences of curing patients online.

On February 4, the National Health Commission held a press conference to announce the death rate of the new type of pneumonia so far: the case fatality rate of the confirmed cases in China is 2.1% , and the case fatality rate of the confirmed cases in Hubei province is 3.1% , confirmed cases in Wuhan, case-fatality rate, 4.9% .

Why are case fatality rates higher in Wuhan than elsewhere? At the press conference, experts said one of the main reasons was the concentration of outbreaks and the shortage of beds.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On Feb. 4, the Fire Mountain Hospital delivered 1,000 new beds, and the Thunder Mountain Hospital is about to deliver 1,500 new beds. At the same time, Wuhan started to build shelter hospitals, with a total of 13 shelter hospitals, which are expected to add more than 10,000 new beds.

Wards are being built all over the country. On January 31, the Public Health Rescue Centre in Changsha was renovated, adding 300 beds to cope with the outbreak. February 1, Beijing Xiaotangshan Hospital to start the renovation project. February 5,00:00, Guizhou Province Staff Hospital was completed, as a new type of pneumonia confirmed and designated treatment hospital to be delivered. On February 6, the Infectious Disease Ward of Zhengzhou's First People's Hospital was completed and delivered. On February 3, the first phase of construction of Xi'an's Public Health Centre, an emergency isolation ward with 500 beds, is due to open in mid-february..

Source: National Institutes of Health

January 31st is a turning point in the statistics of patients who have been diagnosed and admitted to hospital. On that day, the number of people who were diagnosed and cured exceeded the number of deaths.

As of 11:00 a.m. on February 5,892 people had been cured, 260 more had been cured, 492 had died, and 67 more had died.

All over the country and overseas have also been in succession out of patients cured of the news. On Feb. 4, the first patient in the United States to be diagnosed with new pneumonia was discharged and treated with the anti-ebola Drug Redesavir.

The drug is still in the clinical research and development stage, has been introduced into China, Emergency Start Phase III clinical trials.

On February 1, the DT financial analysis of all public reports found that cured and discharged patients were generally younger than the infected population, that the cured patients received treatment for slightly longer periods than the dead, and that most of the dead did not survive a treatment cycle, so to win the COVID-19, "it's important to get through the first week of treatment. " .

This is in line with data released by the National Health Commission on Feb. 4: The average length of stay for discharged patients is just over nine days, and the average length of stay in Hubei Province is 20 days. "The first is related to the more severe cases, and the second is related to the more stringent discharge criteria set by the Wuhan, " experts said

Zhou Xin, a professor of breathing medicine at the Shanghai First People's Hospital and the head of the medical team of the Shanghai aid-hubei medical team, worked in the first-line Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital to fight the "epidemic, " said in an interview on February 1, "This new type of pneumonia, 80% is mild, one to two weeks after medication can be recovered, " "the elderly and basic diseases, generally easy to aggravate.
